{"questionId":"12275","questionHtml":"<p>If <strong><em>A</em></strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  x&amp;4 \\\\   4&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <strong><em>B</em></strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  2&amp;y \\\\   8&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, find 2 values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>, given that <strong><em>AB</em></strong> = <strong><em>BA</em></strong>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>AB</em></strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  x&amp;4 \\\\   4&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right)\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  2&amp;y \\\\   8&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right) = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {2x + 32}&amp;{xy + 16} \\\\   {24}&amp;{4y + 8}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>32</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>16</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>24</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>8</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>BA</em></strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  2&amp;y \\\\   8&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right)\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  x&amp;4 \\\\   4&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right) = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {2x + 4y}&amp;{2y + 8} \\\\   {8x + 16}&amp;{40}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>8</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>8</mn>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>16</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>40</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>AB</em></strong> = <strong><em>BA</em></strong> ⇒ 8<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;+ 16 = 24 and 4<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;+ 8 = 40</p>\n<p>This gives <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 8\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n</math></span>.<strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong><strong><em>&nbsp; (C3)</em></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12275","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.46","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"If A = ( x 4 4 2 ) and B = ( 2 y 8 4 ) , find 2 values of x and y , given that AB = BA.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"46","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}